whereas.text:
Whereas Sikhism is a religion founded in the Punjab region
			 of South Asia over five centuries ago and introduced to the United States in
			 the 19th century;

Whereas Sikhism is the fifth largest world religion with
			 approximately 25 million adherents from diverse backgrounds throughout the
			 world, including 500,000 adherents in the United States;

Whereas Vaisakhi is one of the most religiously
			 significant days in Sikh history, commemorating the creation of the Khalsa, a
			 fellowship of devout Sikhs, by Guru Gobind Singh in 1699;
